The content of the seminars is related to the objectives and learning outcomes of the course. Seminars are dedicated to sub-topics of the master's thesis proposal. An important role is given to discussions, feedback to each others' homeworks. Students get individual feedback to their projects and problems that emerge in the course of planning their research. Sub-topics covered at the seminars also depend on individual research interests of the students of the particular year.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The objective of the course is to prepare master's students for independent research and to give feedback to their projects. The focus is on different stages related to planning a master's studies research, specific problems involved in each stage are discussed in detail. The ability to motivate oneself and plan one's work independently is promoted. As the result of the course each student writes up an independent master's thesis research proposal.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After successful completion of the course the student is able to: plan an independent research project focusing on a manageable research topic during the master's studies formulate research questions critically analyse the literature related to the topic plan the collection and analysis of the empirical material draft the schedule of the research process use motivation techniques
